<title>Planning and preparation</title>

000576_2a0a837c-ea59-bb3d-00d0-1449774c6f91
may contain ambiguous provision: Not all characteristics of an item or a subject can be or need to be standardized
<p id="_2a0a837c-ea59-bb3d-00d0-1449774c6f91">Not all characteristics of an item or a subject can be or need to be standardized. The choice of characteristics to be standardized depends on the aims of the document (e.g. health, safety, protection of the environment, interface, interchangeability, compatibility or interworking, and variety control). A functional analysis of the product can help to identify the characteristics to be included in the document.</p>
2

Example may contain requirement: Design requirements: The table shall have four wooden legs

</example>

000638_65abade7-0fd2-be71-edf5-d9bf9846a675
may contain ambiguous provision: If a test method is, or is likely to be, applicable to two or more types of product, a document shall be prepared on the method itself, and each document dealing with a given product shall refer to it (indicating any modifications that could be necessary)
<p id="_65abade7-0fd2-be71-edf5-d9bf9846a675">If a test method is, or is likely to be, applicable to two or more types of product, a document shall be prepared on the method itself, and each document dealing with a given product shall refer to it (indicating any modifications that could be necessary). This will help to prevent unnecessary deviations.</p>

<clause id="cls_7" inline-header="false" obligation="normative">
<title>Verbal forms for expressions of provisions</title>
<clause id="_general" inline-header="false" obligation="normative">
<title>General</title>
<p id="_ed5424ef-cd8e-e81e-cba2-dedf680f0c1e">The user of the document needs to be able to identify the requirements he/she is obliged to satisfy in order to claim compliance with a document. The user also needs to be able to distinguish these requirements from other types of provision where there is a choice (i.e. recommendations, permissions, possibilities and capabilities).</p>

000955table_5
may contain ambiguous provision: Do not use “might” instead of “may” in this context
<td colspan="2" valign="top" align="left">Do not use “possible” or “impossible” in this context.<br/> Do not use “can” instead of “may” in this context. <br/> Do not use “might” instead of “may” in this context. <br/> “May” signifies permission expressed by the document, whereas “can” refers to the ability of a user of the document or to a possibility open to him/her. <br/> The French verb “pouvoir” can indicate both permission and possibility. If there is a risk of misunderstanding, the use of other expressions is advisable.</td>

001094_ee73a589-af2e-eea3-fb26-1a66d090503e
All lists must be preceded by colon or full stop: Representation of numbers and numerical values
<ul id="_ee73a589-af2e-eea3-fb26-1a66d090503e"> <li> <p id="_4691cc22-25bb-8103-4ce1-8201b08abbe7">The decimal sign shall be a comma on the line in all language versions.</p>
</li>

Appropriate measures shall be taken to avoid ingestion. Care shall be taken in the disposal of these solutions. <br/> WARNING — Too high a temperature increase can cause a vigorous, exothermic reaction in the digestion solution with a high pressure increase and blow-off of the security valve. Losses of analytes are possible. <br/> WARNING — This test involves handling of hot apparatus. In addition, for some iron ores, spitting can occur when loading the sample into the hot container. <br/> WARNING — The reagents used in this method are strongly corrosive and partly very toxic. Safety precautions are absolutely necessary, not only due to the strong corrosive reagents, but also to high temperature and high pressure.</p>

<title>Purpose or rationale</title>
<p id="_98559fdb-f13d-e201-7c39-2e7e4e7f4dc8">Annexes are used to provide additional information to the main body of the document and are developed for several reasons, for example:</p>
2



002495_2bef3a7e-df89-d53f-60da-bac65bf84797
may contain ambiguous provision: For example, a test method that is optional may contain requirements but there is no need to comply with these requirements to claim compliance with the document
<p id="_2bef3a7e-df89-d53f-60da-bac65bf84797">Informative annexes provide additional information intended to assist the understanding or use of the document. Informative annexes may contain optional requirements. For example, a test method that is optional may contain requirements but there is no need to comply with these requirements to claim compliance with the document. The status of the annex (informative or normative) shall be made clear by the way in which it is referred to in the text and shall be stated under the heading of the annex.</p>

NOTE   Individuals may have more than one function …
“may” constitutes a permission

<title>Purpose or rationale</title>
<p id="_cc28c6c2-3db1-c091-98ce-0debeb709213">Examples illustrate concepts presented in the document. The document shall be usable without the examples.</p>

002860_de6ac88c-50a6-43cc-533b-246e676d7350
may contain ambiguous provision: Examples do not need to have a title, but they can, if necessary, be grouped into a clause or subclause entitled “Example” or “Examples” (see , which is titled “Examples”).
<p id="_de6ac88c-50a6-43cc-533b-246e676d7350">Examples do not need to have a title, but they can, if necessary, be grouped into a clause or subclause entitled “Example” or “Examples” (see <xref target="scls_25-6"/>, which is titled “Examples”).</p>
2



002865_a90f0314-9554-1b7b-ca6e-f010fe5d3c88
may contain ambiguous provision: A single example in a subdivision does not need to be numbered.​
<p id="_a90f0314-9554-1b7b-ca6e-f010fe5d3c88">Within a given clause or subclause, examples shall be numbered sequentially. The numbering restarts at each new subdivision. A single example in a subdivision does not need to be numbered.</p>

002870_6501547a-d61b-13f3-6fbf-2b15309e1204

Scope must occur before Terms and Definitions

<title>Tables</title>
<clause id="scls_29-1" inline-header="false" obligation="normative">
<title>Purpose or rationale</title>
<p id="_7d95d205-69b8-da18-c62b-5e147cae80c0">Tables are used when they are the most efficient means of presenting information in an easily comprehensible form.</p>

003575_c29711eb-9fcd-d524-fcdc-359b0d5e2f3b
may contain ambiguous provision: Notes to tables do not need to be referred to.
<p id="_c29711eb-9fcd-d524-fcdc-359b0d5e2f3b">Notes to tables shall not contain requirements or any information considered indispensable for the use of the document. Any requirements relating to the content of a table shall be given in the text, in a footnote to the table or as a paragraph within the table. Notes to tables do not need to be referred to.</p>

<p id="_eb2851fe-6bc4-1bc3-b948-7f52c5f0eb23">Where patent rights have been identified during the preparation of the document, they shall be included in the Introduction.</p>
2



003702cls_31
Scope must occur before Terms and Definitions
<clause id="cls_31" inline-header="false" obligation="normative">
<title>Use of trade names and trademarks</title>
<p id="_63c5cc57-2214-2012-f6ce-ad03b2d909e1">A correct designation or description of a product shall be given rather than a trade name or trademark.</p>

<p id="_df6feab8-d852-7729-6fc7-4fc1d2380480">Proprietary trade names or trademarks for a particular product should as far as possible be avoided, even if they are in common use.</p>
2



003715ex_30-2
Example may contain permission: Equivalent products may be used if they can be shown to lead to the same results
<example id="ex_30-2"> <p id="_12b4ea41-9521-c460-b7e3-82e03d1b5e90">… [trade name or trademark of product] … is the [trade name or trademark] of a product supplied by … [supplier] …. This information is given for the convenience of users of this document and does not constitute an endorsement by … [ISO or IEC] … of the product named. Equivalent products may be used if they can be shown to lead to the same results.</p>
</example>
2

003735cls_33
Scope must occur before Terms and Definitions
<clause id="cls_33" inline-header="false" obligation="normative">
<title>Aspects of conformity assessment</title>
<clause id="scls_33-1" inline-header="false" obligation="normative">
<title>Documents containing requirements for products, processes, services, persons, systems and bodies</title>
<p id="_0d16ec10-f998-e465-63b8-24b3157445a9">All documents containing requirements for products, processes, services, persons, systems and bodies shall be written in accordance with the “neutrality principle”, such that conformity can be assessed by a manufacturer or supplier (first party), a user or purchaser (second party), or an independent body (third party).<note id="_57561b32-ba9d-6e8b-1db5-056cc273a9d3"> <p id="_521f627c-081a-c265-3296-e611c526c31c">First-party, second-party and third-party conformity assessment activities are defined in ISO/IEC 17000.</p>

004020_e3cf5b6e-ac8c-6e52-132c-b3da0f732efa
language-specific abbreviation: ppm
<p id="_e3cf5b6e-ac8c-6e52-132c-b3da0f732efa">Wherever possible, language-specific abbreviated terms should not be used. When language-specific abbreviated terms which are in common use, such as ppm, are used, their meaning shall be explained.</p>

004085_1742a255-ee48-89c5-2c2d-af35d76fc711
may contain ambiguous provision: Note that quantity values having the same unit might nevertheless belong to a quantity of a different kind (e.g
<p id="_1742a255-ee48-89c5-2c2d-af35d76fc711">Two or more quantity values cannot be added or subtracted, unless they all belong to a quantity of the same kind (e.g. diameter, circumference and wavelength are quantities of the same kind, called “length”).<br/> Note that quantity values having the same unit might nevertheless belong to a quantity of a different kind (e.g. both “action” and “angular momentum” have the SI unit J s, but are not of the same kind and thus cannot be added or subtracted).</p>

004100_e6e8a4d5-a3bf-596b-4943-84c72dc8aa43
may contain ambiguous provision: Do not write “log” in mathematical formulae if the base needs to be specified
<p id="_e6e8a4d5-a3bf-596b-4943-84c72dc8aa43">Do not write “log” in mathematical formulae if the base needs to be specified. Write “lg”, “ln”, “lb” or “<asciimath>log_a</asciimath>”.</p>

004156_b4c4c719-e7f4-c9a5-e3b4-6982b433e71c
may contain ambiguous provision: A designation system does not need to appear in every document that contains elements of choice
<p id="_b4c4c719-e7f4-c9a5-e3b4-6982b433e71c">A designation system does not need to appear in every document that contains elements of choice. It is particularly useful for product and material documents. The committee may choose whether to include a designation system.</p>
2



004173_ba602b44-ef1c-446c-87da-6cee0e1429a3
List entry of separate sentences must end with full stop: A document in which more than one choice is open in relation to a characteristic defined in the document.​
The choice from a range of alternative dimensions or other properties in a specification for a product; the choice of a particular test method in a generic document covering a variety of methods for determining the value of a given characteristic of a product; the choice of specific values of certain testing parameters of which a number of alternatives are offered in the document.​ [For product or material standards,  also applies.]​

may contain ambiguous provision: In the individual item block, letters I and O shall be avoided because they could lead to confusion with the numerical digits “one” and “zero”.

004419_ff2b2497-50e7-a592-ff45-38cecb393ab7
Example may contain permission: If the international designation of a screw is

Slotted pan screw ISO 1580-M5  20-4,8

its national designation may be

Slotted pan screw VN 4183-ISO 1580-M5  20-4,8

if VN 4183 is the identification of the national standard corresponding to ISO 1580 which has been adopted without change
<example id="_ff2b2497-50e7-a592-ff45-38cecb393ab7"> <p id="_bfd1126f-aa48-c70d-240f-abd5498f26d4">If the international designation of a screw is</p>

<p id="_788a26b5-696d-f2fa-0fc4-558d42e6c824">Slotted pan screw ISO 1580-M5 <asciimath>xx</asciimath> 20-4,8</p>

<p id="_df94b26c-aea9-516d-8270-06a1ff77d212">its national designation may be</p>
